com.camerontec.catalys.server.security.auth.login

Class FixLoginCallbackHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.security.auth.login.FixLoginCallbackHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CallbackHandler

    public class FixLoginCallbackHandler
extends Object
implements CallbackHandler
    General purpose FIX login authentication callback handler.

    This class understands the following callback types:

    • NameCallback - username retrieval
    • PasswordCallback - password retrieval
    • TextOutputCallback - in order that the LoginModule can pass a message back to the authenticator
    • TagValueCallback - generic tag/value retrieval from the FIX logon message
    • ConnectionPointCallback - session connection point retrieval.

    On logon failure the owner of this callback may query it for an output message which may have been passed back from a LoginModule (although this depends on the login module implementation) via getOutputMessage(). Note that the getOutputMessage() method has read once semantics; the output message is cleared after the first read.
